  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nTransaction history doesn't always work right and when it does, it depends on external services such as Infura or Etherscan. Specifically:\r\n\r\n- transaction history depends on etherscan API - this is a centralization point which means that etherscan is treates as a trusted entity. Also, failure to reach etherscan API (e.g. when it is blocked by the ISP or even local proxy) would result in a failure to update the history.\r\n\r\n-token transfer event history depends on Infura and strictly speaking doesn't really work since a recent change in their infrastructure. We are now displaying only the token transfers for the last two weeks.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nThe solution needs to:\r\n- only depend on the data accessible from the ethereum client - blockchain state and event log\r\n  - allowed exception - service that obtains asset prices in fiat - it has to be an external service, but failure to reach it should be handled gracefully\r\n- have a reasonable performance, possibly obtained by smart request paging and pre-loading\r\n\r\nUnknown factors: LES implementation\r\n    \r\n",
